    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1861-09-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1861-09-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="154" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d154">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Seward</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Dayton</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 59.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of
                                    State</hi>,<lb/>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1861-09-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 23, 1861</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your despatch of the 29th of August (No.
                            37) was duly received.</p>
                <p>The proceedings it relates had, however, been anticipated, and it only
                            remains to be said in regard to them, that your conduct therein is fully
                            approved</p>
                <p>I am, sir, respectfully, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William. L. Dayton</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c</hi>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
